rily based on the Northern Ireland Transcribed Corpus of Speech, but also on the FRED and SED data (Survey of English Dialects) for the North of England. Susanne Wagner is concerned with the phenomenon of pronominal gender, focussing especially on the typologically rather unique semantic gender system in the dialects of Southwest England. This volume will be of interest to dialectologists, sociolinguists, typologists, historical linguists, grammarians, and anyone interested in the structure of spontaneous spoken English.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aEnglish languagexAgreement. 0aEnglish languagexDialectszGreat Britain. 0aEnglish languagexRelative clauses. 0aEnglish languagezGreat BritainxGrammar. 4aDialektologie. 4aEnglisch/ Sprache. 4aGrammatik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aDialectology.  aEnglish/ language.  agrammar.1 aHerrmann, Tanja, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHerrmann, Tanja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKortmann, Bernd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPietsch, Lukas, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPietsch, Lukas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWagner, Susanne, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWagner, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Linguistics and Semiotics  2000-2014 (EN)z978311023845708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part o